<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAR 93 / World News in Brief: Doctor dismisses threat
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Jim Howe, the doctor who treated Hillsborough coma victim Tony Bland,
dismissed as 'foolish' a former priest's threat to launch a private
prosecution against him for murder. Mr Bland died in a West Yorkshire
hospital on Wednesday after a court ruled that his life support systems
could be switched off.
</TEXT>
